Heat oven to 350 degrees F. In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and butter. Stir in dissolved coffee, sweetened condensed milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Pour into pie crust; top with walnuts. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Serve warm or chilled. Top with whipped topping. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.